text: Timothy Alan Huelskamp (; born November 11, 1968) is an American politician. He was the U.S. Representative for from 2011 to 2017. Huelskamp, a member of the Republican Party, was rated the least bipartisan. He ran for re-election in 2016 but was defeated in the Republican primary on August 2, 2016, by Roger Marshall. His term in the House ended on January 3, 2017. ==References== Category:1968 births Category:Living people Category:United States representatives from Kansas Category:Kansas Republicans
